==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Miscegenation
<hw>Mis`ce*ge*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>miscere</ets> to mix + the root of <ets>genus</ets> race.]</ety>
<def>A mixing of races; amalgamation, as by intermarriage of black and
white.</def> <note>Until the late twentieth century,
<ex>misceganation</ex> was a crime in some states of the Southern United
States.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

